SCRAPIE IN JAPAN
-----------------
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: September 1999).
Emergency report
Information received on 22 Oct 2001 from Dr Shigeo Miyajima, Director of
Animal Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo:
Report date: 22 Oct 2001
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory
Date of confirmation of diagnosis: 15 Oct 2001
Outbreaks:
Location Inashiki gun, Ibaraki Prefecture
No. of outbreaks: 1 experimental farm
Description of affected population: a wether in a university experimental farm.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
ovi / 23 / 1 / 1 / 3/ 0
Diagnosis:
- the wether died on 10 May 2001 with dysstasia resulting from a bone fracture;
- in mid September the brain sample was subjected to histopathological
examination and found to have lesions;
- the wether was diagnosed as having scrapie by histopathological and
immunohistochemical examinations at Obihiro University of Agriculture and
Veterinary Medicine, Hokkaido Prefecture.
Source of agent / origin of infection: under investigation.
Control measures:
- the farm has been placed under supervision by Ibaraki Livestock Hygiene
Service Center;
- movement control on all animals that were kept with the infected wether;
- cleaning and disinfection of pens.
